summary: Can you do a fic in which Harry goes back to Holmes Chapel after being on tour and goes to the bakery he used to work at and...
question: Can you do a fic in which Harry goes back to Holmes Chapel after being on tour and goes to the bakery he used to work at and turns out you work there and have a nice convo and decide to meet after your shift ends? Idk, I'm SOFT
answer:
harry feels proper nostalgic.

it’s been months ever since he went back to holmes chapel and maybe even more months ever since he went back to the bakery, and by the looks of it, it’s gonna be a quiet trip since it’s too early in the morning and his mum-like friends that ran it were probably still asleep.

he’s yawning as his hand are all tucked to his pockets, feeling the few crisp notes in it as he opens the door and hears the familiar chime, smiling to himself.

he knows his way around and figures out that there’s some new selections and some’s been pulled out, but he’s actually thankful that they never phased out his favorite croissant, grabbing a couple of them as he puts them in the tray while he hums.

seems to forget the fact that there was someone there because he thinks he’s pissed himself once he turns around and sets the tray down on the counter, clutching his heart.

“holy fuckin’ — w-where did you come from?”

“was just sitting behind register.”

he hears you yawn and he’s received this familiar look from you even though he’s never met you, recognizing that you probably know him as you’re smiling and rubbing your eyes while looking up at him, all before cashing him out.

it was a swift exchange and harry wishes he should’ve gotten more croissants and should’ve stalled longer, mid-way into leaving the bakery as he turns back.

harry smiles to himself, looking down on the floor as he says all the words he’s been thinking of in one go.

“have you eaten breakfast? s’only us, i mean — besides, shift’s an empty one and i haven’t caught your name yet, love.”

summary: #2 - Love me more than I hate myself.
title: #2 - Love me more than I hate myself.
body:
Everybody wants to love someone. Everybody wants to receive love from someone. That’s normal, healthy. Well.. not for everyone. 
So, when exactly desire of feelings isn’t good for us? And how to rightly describe “good” and “bad”?

Do you love yourself? Maybe not completely and perfectly, but do you see yourself like autonomous, beautiful person? Do you like your appearance, the way you behave. Did you tame your demons, maybe defects and you feel like you could live with them? 
If yes, that’s good. You seem like a person that may have kind of healthy relationship.
If not, you should think about it and wonder if all of these things could be an obstacle in your future relationship. If you even don’t like yourself, how can you expect from another person to love you entirely? 
That’s brutal, but it’s true. It would be tiring and hard for everyone to love someone who has no self-confidence and self-love. Your partner won’t fill your lack of love, it’s just a person. Not God, not you. First of all, you should like yourself. Your appearance, your nature, your flaws, mistake. Your past. 

And then, you’ll be ready to accept somebodys’ love.

summary: Wow so that anon with The concept of of really younger y/n and all i could think was him calling her lovie and OH MY GOODNESS...
question: Wow so that anon with The concept of of really younger y/n and all i could think was him calling her lovie and OH MY GOODNESS HOW PRECIOUS AND PROTECTIVE HED BE
answer:
harry would be so precious and protective over his lovie; absolutely no doubt.

he can’t help but to be a mother hen over you sometimes and sometimes he just has to fucking talk to himself because he needs to remember that he doesn’t want to be overbearing, or the fact that he doesn’t want to be the one who you’d hate to be a boyfriend.

he’d be still so soft though, and he’s absolutely smitten with you that he’s just about ready to give anything.

feeling sick? his mum’s on speed-dial while he’s already clutching the right medicine that he’s already asked the doctor of.

feeling nice? would make you feel even nicer and he doesn’t even mind giving you extra joy.

feeling needy? he’s already prepared himself for having you constantly around him looking for affection since you seem to be in a cuddly mood, pajamas all worn and arms all wide.

harry would be protective too and he’d try to put out everything that would bother and harm you out of the way just because he didn’t like seeing you get hurt — or much more even tolerate the thought of you being hurt.

over-all, harry would be the best boyfriend. good night

summary: Rules: write the first ten songs that come up on shuffle (no skipping) and quote your favourite lyric from each song, then tag...
body:
Rules: write the first ten songs that come up on shuffle (no skipping) and quote your favourite lyric from each song, then tag 10 people.

(I was asked by an anon rather than tagged)

1. From the dining table - Harry Styles

“Comfortable silence is so overrated, why won’t you ever be the first one to break?”


2. Just saying - 5sos

“Got a big house, says he lives alone, but when I drove by I could see his mum was home.”


3. She don’t love me - Zayn

“It’s kind of hard to walk right, when you’re walking on my left.”


4. Better than words - One Direction

“Better than words, more than a feeling, crazy in love,”


5. Wherever this goes - the fray

“Find ourselves a bus stop, make our own way.”


6. Seven Wonders - Fleetwood Mac

“If I live to see the seven wonders, I’ll make a path to the rainbows end.”


7. What a feeling - One Direction

“What a feeling to be a king beside you, somehow.”


8. Nobody - Selena Gomez

“Nobody’s ever loved me to the truth, like you ooh.”


9. You’re still the one - Shania Twain

“Ain’t nothing better, we beat the odds together.”


10. Fade into you - Nashville

“If I was the red and you were the blue, I could just fade into you.”


This was so much fun.

I don’t know who to tag but if you want to do it, class this as a tag.
